Finally the F.Moser is done! New painting, restored Shimano 600 tricolor groupset, old and brand new parts..ready to go!

Frame: all pantograph F. Moser model Corsa 54x54 made of Oria GM 0.0 tubing, built in 1987
Fork: F.Moser made of Oria GM 0.0 tubing with the 51.151 logo serigraphy, built in1987
Headset: semi-integrated Shimano 600, 6400 series (HP-6400)
Bottom Brackets: Shimano 600, 6400 series italian threading 36mmx24/115mm (BB-6400)
Crankset: Shimano 600 serie 6400 corone 53-42 (FC-6400)
Pedals: Shimano 600, 6400 series (PD-6400) with Shimano 600 toe clips
Front Derallieur: Shimano 600, 6400 series (FD-6400-B)
Rear Derallieur: Shimano 600, 6400 series (RD-6400)
Shifters: Shimano 600, 6400 series 7sp SIS, Light Action (SL-6400)
Brake Levers: non aero Shimano 600, 6400 series (BL6401)
Brakes: Shimamo 600, 6400 series (BR-6403)
Hubs: Shimano 600, 6400 series (FH-6400 & HB-6400)
Rims: 700c Mavic MA 40, made in France, "EMR7" Stainless Steel Eyelt Hard Anodised Treatement 650v, 36 spoke drillings, for clinchers
Spokes: Alpina Inox
Clinchers: Michelin Dynamic Classic 700x28
Inner tubes: Panasonic Panaracer 700cx25-38c
Cassette: Shimano 600 7v 13-28 (CS-6400-7)
Chain: Shimano 7sp (CN-6400)
Seat Post: lightened San Marco 
Saddle: white leather San Marco Rolls 
Quill: Nitto Young 3 72° 70mm
Handlebar: Sakae Custom Anatomic Bend (Modolo patent) 42 c-c
Bar Tape: Deda TAPE
Cables and Wires: Alligator
